cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of detecting data symbols stored in multi-level-cell (MLC) flash memory, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed solution involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the optimization of read thresholds for LDPC coded flash memory channels, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and embedded systems (cs.ET). Finally, the use of RNNs for soft-decision decoding of error-correction codes is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE).
